"eula.body" = "Abysso End User License Agreement (EULA)\n\n1. Overview\nAbysso (\"the Software\") is a utility that helps clean and manage storage on macOS. By agreeing to these terms, you agree to use the Software under the conditions below.\n\n2. Responsibility for Data Deletion\nThe Software provides features to delete caches, logs, large files, applications, and related files. Except for the Delete Completely and Empty Trash features, most deletions go through the Trash and are recoverable. However, files deleted with the 'Delete Completely (secure delete)' feature cannot be recovered. You are responsible for verifying the items you delete, and the developer is not liable for any data loss resulting from deletion.\n\n3. System Changes\nThe Software can enable or disable login items, startup programs, and auto-launch entries, and can run maintenance tasks (freeing memory, flushing the DNS cache, re-indexing Spotlight). These actions may affect system behavior.\n\n4. Disclaimer of Warranty\nThe Software is provided \"as-is\", without warranty of any kind, express or implied. All risk arising from use of the Software is borne by you.\n\n5. Limitation of Liability\nUnder no circumstances shall the developer be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use or inability to use the Software.\n\nIf you do not agree to these terms, you may not use the Software.";

